Task: UI Personalization & Menu Implementation
Assign Unique Object Identity (setObjectName)

Description: Assigned a specific ID ("HlavniPozadi") to the main widget. This acts as a CSS selector, allowing the stylesheet to target the main background specifically without accidentally restyling the buttons or text fields.

Implement Contextual Dropdown Menu (QMenu)

Description: Created a popup menu container to house multiple user choices. This prevents the UI from being cluttered with too many buttons by hiding options inside a single menu.

Configure Dynamic Menu Actions (addAction)

Description: Populated the menu with selectable color options ("Červená", "Modrá", etc.). Used Lambda functions to pass specific hex color codes or names to the coloring logic whenever a user selects an item.

Link Menu to Control Button (setMenu)

Description: Attached the created QMenu to the existing btn_menu. This converts the button into a dropdown trigger, enabling a cleaner and more professional user interaction.

Develop Background Customization Logic (zmen_barvu)

Description: Created a custom method to handle visual updates. It accepts a color string and applies it to the UI, ensuring the internal state of the theme stays synchronized with the user's choice.

Enable Custom Background Rendering (setAttribute)

Description: Enabled the WA_StyledBackground attribute. This is a technical requirement for QWidget subclasses to ensure they correctly render background colors defined via CSS (Stylesheets) rather than the default system theme.

Apply Global Styling and Branding (setStyleSheet)

Description: Injected a block of CSS-like code to define the application's "Look and Feel." This includes:

Typography: Setting large, bold fonts (70px) for the score.

Transparency: Using rgba colors for a modern, semi-transparent look.

Shape: Implementing border-radius to create rounded corners for a sleek, modern interface.
